<br>
 There are inherit flaws in both socialism and capitalism. In socialism you find that ~some~ people are just willing to do nothing, because they know that their basic needs will be met, so they are willing to let others work to support them. Let's call this : Laziness.<br>
<br>
 In capitalism ~some~ people (maybe ~most~) of the rich are willing to sell their own grandmother to make a 2 cent profit and they really don't care if their economic style means that MILLIONS live under bridges with no food or health care. Let's call this : Greed.<br>
<br>
 There SHOULD be some sort of balance met so that everyone's basic human needs are met, whilst at the same time, those that work hard, or take economic risks are rewarded for what they do....<br>
<br>
 As a footnote, I ~am~ embarrassed that I live in the richest country in the world and we FAIL to offer a minimuim health care program to those that are economically disenfranchised.<br>
